summary: A U.S. Customs and Border Protection TECS Person Encounter List detailing the extensive international travel history of Ghislaine Maxwell from 1991 to 1999. The document, generated in 2020, lists 58 flight entries, showing frequent travel between the U.S. (primarily JFK, MIA) and Europe (primarily London, Paris).

keyFacts: The document is a law enforcement travel history report for Ghislaine Maxwell, generated by CBP in January 2020.
It records 58 international flights taken by Maxwell between 1991 and 1999, demonstrating a high frequency of transatlantic travel.
Primary travel hubs were New York (JFK), Miami (MIA), London (LHR/LGW), and Paris (CDG/ORY), with a few flights to/from Australia (SYD).
The document shows Maxwell used both a passport (P) and a U.S. Alien Registration Card (A) for travel during this period.
The data was pulled from the TECS system, a primary law enforcement and border security database used by DHS.
